Introduction

Base URL: http://shopking.test

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Authenticating requests

This API is not authenticated.

Endpoints

Display Swagger API page.

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://shopking.test/api/documentation" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://shopking.test/api/documentation"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (200):

Show headers 
cache-control: no-cache, private
content-type: application/json
access-control-allow-origin: *

Example: application/json

Display Oauth2 callback pages.

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://shopking.test/api/oauth2-callback" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://shopking.test/api/oauth2-callback"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (200):

Show headers 
content-type: text/html; charset=UTF-8
cache-control: no-cache, private
access-control-allow-origin: *
 

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en-US">
<head>
    <title>Swagger UI: OAuth2 Redirect</title>
</head>
<body>
<script>
    'use strict';
    function run () {
        var oauth2 = window.opener.swaggerUIRedirectOauth2;
        var sentState = oauth2.state;
        var redirectUrl = oauth2.redirectUrl;
        var isValid, qp, arr;

        if (/code|token|error/.test(window.location.hash)) {
            qp = window.location.hash.substring(1).replace('?', '&');
        } else {
            qp = location.search.substring(1);
        }

        arr = qp.split("&");
        arr.forEach(function (v,i,_arr) { _arr[i] = '"' + v.replace('=', '":"') + '"';});
        qp = qp ? JSON.parse('{' + arr.join() + '}',
                function (key, value) {
                    return key === "" ? value : decodeURIComponent(value);
                }
        ) : {};

        isValid = qp.state === sentState;

        if ((
          oauth2.auth.schema.get("flow") === "accessCode" ||
          oauth2.auth.schema.get("flow") === "authorizationCode" ||
          oauth2.auth.schema.get("flow") === "authorization_code"
        ) && !oauth2.auth.code) {
            if (!isValid) {
                oauth2.errCb({
                    authId: oauth2.auth.name,
                    source: "auth",
                    level: "warning",
                    message: "Authorization may be unsafe, passed state was changed in server. The passed state wasn't returned from auth server."
                });
            }

            if (qp.code) {
                delete oauth2.state;
                oauth2.auth.code = qp.code;
                oauth2.callback({auth: oauth2.auth, redirectUrl: redirectUrl});
            } else {
                let oauthErrorMsg;
                if (qp.error) {
                    oauthErrorMsg = "["+qp.error+"]: " +
                        (qp.error_description ? qp.error_description+ ". " : "no accessCode received from the server. ") +
                        (qp.error_uri ? "More info: "+qp.error_uri : "");
                }

                oauth2.errCb({
                    authId: oauth2.auth.name,
                    source: "auth",
                    level: "error",
                    message: oauthErrorMsg || "[Authorization failed]: no accessCode received from the server."
                });
            }
        } else {
            oauth2.callback({auth: oauth2.auth, token: qp, isValid: isValid, redirectUrl: redirectUrl});
        }
        window.close();
    }

    if (document.readyState !== 'loading') {
        run();
    } else {
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
            run();
        });
    }
</script>
</body>
</html>
Received response:
Request failed with error:

Accept

Body Parameters

POST api/admin/setting/product-category

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://shopking.test/api/admin/setting/product-category" \
    --header "Content-Type: multipart/form-data" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --form "name=l"\
    --form "parent_id=ninsxye"\
    --form "description=Aspernatur ratione enim quasi itaque iusto rerum unde asperiores."\
    --form "status=12"\
    --form "image=@C:\Users\APON\AppData\Local\Temp\php7E30.tmp" 
const url = new URL(
    "http://shopking.test/api/admin/setting/product-category"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "multipart/form-data",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

const body = new FormData();
body.append('name', 'l');
body.append('parent_id', 'ninsxye');

    --header "Accept: application/json" \

    --form "description=Atque et cum et."\
    --form "menu_section_id=8381.8177"\
    --form "menu_template_id=1890229"\
    --form "status=1"\
    --form "image=@C:\Users\APON\AppData\Local\Temp\php7F82.tmp"

);

};

body.append('description', 'Atque et cum et.');
body.append('menu_section_id', '8381.8177');
body.append('menu_template_id', '1890229');
body.append('status', '1');

body.append('meta_keyword', 'pta');

Must not be greater than 190 characters. Example: pta

image   file  optional  

Must be an image. Must not be greater than 2048 kilobytes. Example: C:\Users\APON\AppData\Local\Temp\php8373.tmp

POST api/admin/damage

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://shopking.test/api/admin/damage" \
    --header "Content-Type: multipart/form-data" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --form "date=sed"\
    --form "subtotal=5055.66"\
    --form "discount=1952449.03408"\
    --form "tax=2342.93106137"\
    --form "total=42.47"\
    --form "note=dowqlhbsaoiswiup"\
    --form "products=["reprehenderit","minus"]"\
    --form "file=@C:\Users\APON\AppData\Local\Temp\php88BB.tmp" 
const url = new URL(
    "http://shopking.test/api/admin/damage"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "multipart/form-data",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

const body = new FormData();
body.append('date', 'sed');
body.append('subtotal', '5055.66');
body.append('discount', '1952449.03408');
body.append('tax', '2342.93106137');
body.append('total', '42.47');
body.append('note', 'dowqlhbsaoiswiup');
body.append('products', '["reprehenderit","minus"]');
body.append('file', document.querySelector('input[name="file"]').files[0]);

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body,
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:

If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
